The Punk Singer
7.4
AdvertisementBy NICOLAS RAPOLDOpens on Friday in New York and Los Angeles.Directed by Sini Anderson1 hour 12 minutes; not ratedKathleen Hanna, the feminist punk hero of the 1990s and beyond, is the main event of the fast-moving documentary To a certain extent, the building up feels like pent-up recompense for the hostility that Ms. Hanna faced and confronted. From early poetry performances through Bikini Kill’s Ms. Hanna herself appears in new interviews and in footage showing her dealing with the effects of Lyme disease. (The illness led to her uncharacteristic quiet during the mid-2000s.) The film shifts gears from the Bikini Kill parts to depict Ms. Hanna’s creativity and force are catching. But other voices are needed to evaluate her achievements with a fuller sense of cultural context and perspective.




